modemu2k is a Hayes-style AT-command modem
emulator that bridges a serial interface to
a TCP or Telnet endpoint over IPv4 or IPv6.
Ships as a C library (libmodemu2k) plus a
small CLI that allocates a PTY and forks a
comm program (minicom, picocom) on the slave,
or accepts an incoming TCP connection as
the TTY. Based on modemu, by Toru Egashira
(1995-1996).
